  "status": "Stagnant",
  "summary": "This EIP proposes a standard for creating \"hooks\" that allow a smart contract function to be called automatically in response to a trigger fired by another contract, by using a public relayer network as a messaging bus. While there are many similar solutions in existence already, this proposal describes a simple yet powerful primitive that can be employed by many applications in an open, permissionless and decentralized manner. It relies on two interfaces, one for a publisher contract and one for a subscriber contract. The publisher contract emits events that are picked up by \"relayers\", who are independent entities that subscribe to \"hook\" events on publisher contracts, and call a function on the respective subscriber contracts, whenever a hook event is fired by the publisher contracts. W",
  "title": "Smart Contract Event Hooks"
}